<p class="large-date-first">April  24,  2019</p><h2>From Ops to DevOps</h2><p class="large-desc">Internal Transformation As a central function, developers must come to us for infrastructure design and hosting.  We are there to ensure that all deployments adhere to policies and standards. Change could only happen as fast as we could deliver it.  Although we increased the throughput of services, we couldn't guarantee it.  Occasional spikes in workload (such as WannaCry) caused delays to projects. Work in Progress We needed to understand and control the work in progress.  Rate of change slows over time due to an increasing body of policy (such as security policies getting stronger&#8230;</p><a href="https://atos.net/en/blog/from-ops-to-devops" title="From Ops to DevOps" class="button-blue">READ MORE</a></div></div>
